<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67cd0bf-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7318"><num value="7318">§ 7318.</num><heading> Radiotelegraph operators on Great Lakes</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf67cd0c0-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7318/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> A radiotelegraph operator on the Great Lakes only shall have a first-class or second-class radiotelegraph operator’s license issued by the Federal Communications Commission.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf67cd0c1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7318/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> An endorsement as radiotelegraph operator on the Great Lakes only ends if the holder ceases to hold the license issued by the Commission.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf67cd0c2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/545">97 Stat. 545</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
